The paper discusses a novel subgradient method for matrix optimization problems with nuclear norm regularization. This involves techniques such as stochastic subgradients and incremental SVD updates, which are commonly used in machine learning and optimization (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of efficient linear algebra operations on small matrices, which suggests numerical analysis (cs.NA) as another possible category. The application of the method to matrix completion problems (cs.CV) and the emphasis on practicality and efficiency (cs.DS, cs.SI) further support these categories.
